"The year 2011 will be remembered for a number of very high-profile hacking episodes. RSA, rather notoriously, had its SecurID product compromised by what it insists were state-sponsored hackers. Sony and others came under sustained attack from hacktivists Anonymous and LulzSec. But the first of the firms to be hit in such a public way was HBGary, led by founder and CEO Greg Hoglund, which supplies security services to government and large corporate clients."
